## dfm - dataframe manipulation

Makes namedrop obsolete.  dfm allows commandline manipulation of a log file
read into a pandas dataframe.  Add, delete, keep columns or filter rows based
on a regex.  Rows can be filtered using a regex on columns or an ip filter.

o 2do traffic patterns can be tagged using cmd: f=tag:rulebase,src,dst[,port]

## ilf - ip log filter

Helper module used by dfm for ip filtering using a firewall-like rulebase with
src,dst,port,action,tag.


## PYTEST

Simply run pytest from the project's root dir, e.g. ~/dev/jabs

```
$ sudo pip3 install -U pytest
```

